  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>Yes</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study is designed to investigate biomarkers related to bone turnover in diabetics with
      charcot foot. This is done by measuring local blood samples in the feet, and systemically in
      a vene and an artery. Measurements are done before and after cooling the feet in icewater to
      lower the bloodflow.

      Patients will be compared with healthy diabetic controls.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
